column15: I would prefer it if the pathways and dependencies were shown as suggestions while I'm studying a certain content so that I know what to look for if I'm not understanding the content. Also,  it would be nice if there difference between the pathways are shown (either visually or qualitatively).
It's a little bit confusing what should I expect to see, and if I don't have the hints, I might not know that there are videos to see.

Several suggestions: 1. Introduce a topological ordering option in the score table. 2. If I am taking this course, it would be difficult for me to tell the difference between the pathways and choose one to follow. Would it be possible to provide some descriptions (e.g., most efficient, most comfortable) in each pathway (instead of just naming pathway 1, pathway 2).

1. When mouse pointer is hovered over a node, some dependency links are highlighted, maybe it is better to also highlight the corresponding numbers indicating strength.
2. I am not sure whether showing the average scores is helpful for students to learn. Maybe students just focus on getting a high score instead of mastering the knowledge. But if you do want to show scores, it may be better to show SD too.
It  will be better if there are some explanations about the meaning of weights in the dependency graph. Otherwise it is somehow unnecessary(for me I don't know what those numbers mean)
